Q: HOW BIG ARE THESE PICKS? 
A: My guitar picks are approximately 
 1 1/16 inch or 26 mm wide
 1 1/2 inch long or 31 mm
 1/8 of an inch thick or 3 mm thick to insure durability and to allow the grooves at the top of the pick to be deeper, allowing for better grip
Some guitar picks may not be exactly those dimensions. But I do my best to make them as close to those measurements as I can. I do this by hand and I have to estimate as I sand them by hand. 
Q. CAN YOU ACTUALLY PLAY WITH THESE?
A: Yes, wood guitar picks offer a great sound on pretty much all kinds of guitars.
Feel and sound:
For sound,
They make a great smooth sound when they hit the strings. It doesn't have that plasticky sound that a plastic pick has as it rolls off each string. Customers and friends say that they make a beautiful sound.
For feel,
Smooth to the touch, great grip at the top. It's hard to see in the pictures, but there are indentations at the top on both sides for gripping. Engravings add some roughness but give more friction to make it even easier to grip.
Check to see pictures of the indentations for the grip at the top of the pick at my about page:
https://www.etsy.com/shop/PickslaysWoodworking/about?ref=l2-about
[DIFFERENCE BETWEEN PLASTIC AND WOOD PICKS]
 Wood has no flexibility and is very firm.
  Wood offers a much clearer and stronger strum
  It doesn't have that plastic plucking sound that most plastic picks have as the pick catches on every string. 
  It gives a great sound.

the above picture is a stock photo,
however, other picks will compare in quality, color, and grain pattern

Spencer

Product name: VSCO Cam M5 inspired Lightroom Presets by SNC
Description:
This Lightroom preset allows you to achieve the bright matte look of VSCO Cam M5 in high resolution. It also comes with 2 extra versions of the M5 preset to allow you to achieve a range of looks: a M- (decreased) version, for a subtle edit; and a M (increased) version, for a more dramatic edit. 
*ALSO AVAILABLE IN VALUE BUNDLE WITH OTHER PRESETS*
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________
//COMPATIBILITY//
   -  Best results are with RAW/DNG files. Results with Jpeg files are unpredictable.
   -  Works in Lightroom 5-6 (CC) 
   -  ACR version available
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________
// INSTRUCTIONS AND TROUBLESHOOTING // 
Installing: 
After downloading presets into your folder of choice, open Lightroom and right-click on the folder you want to import the preset into. Click 'import', and select the downloaded preset. 
Using the preset: 
Get the right colour temperature and exposure in your image first, then click on the preset for the edit. You may need to increase or decrease the exposure after the edit has been applied. 
A NOTE ON EXPOSURE: I generally shoot slightly underexposed to optimise skin tones in my portraits- I will usually apply the preset first, then slowly increase exposure, over shoot, then decrease until the colours and skin tones feel right. If your image looks overly contrasty or muddy, an increase in exposure usually helps. 
_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________
*NOTE: Etsy takes 2 business days to process credit card payments before download is made available. Payments through Paypal allow instant download.*
See more examples of this (and other presets) on my blog http://www.jennywuphotography.com/straight-no-chaser/
note: Due to the nature of digital downloads there are no refunds.

You will not receive the exact slices pictured. 
The slices will have a natural strong odor until they dry. This is typical with most types of fresh cut wood slices. The slices will show saw marks, and not be perfectly even and still have some degree of moisture, usually below 40%.
Slices should be separated and air dried after receiving. Drying time can vary by location and other factors, such as, temperature, humidity. If these are for an event please allow for drying time when ordering. 
As the slices dry there can be cracking, checking and loss of bark, this is a natural process and adds character to the pieces. To help slow the natural cracking process a sealant can be applied after they dry some.
We try to provide quality fresh cut wood slices at a reasonable price to our customers. We inspect each slice for quality before shipping.
We are not responsible for any cracking, checking or loss of bark that may occur during the natural drying process. We are not responsible for any odor that occurs with fresh cut wood while it is going through its natural drying process. These things are natural with fresh cut wood and we have no control over it.
These are fresh cut after an order is placed and have a 3 to 5 day handling time. We ship using USPS or FedEx. Shipping to the lower 48 states only. Shipping is not available to Alaska/Hawaii, US Protectorates, APO/FPO, PO Boxes.
